Package dev.kkorolyov.simplestructs.procedure

Class ShortestPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.kkorolyov.simplestructs.procedure.ShortestPath
  • public final class ShortestPath
extends java.lang.Object
    Factory of shortest path procedures on a graph. Each procedure accepts (start, end) arguments and returns a list of nodes denoting the shortest path from start to end.

        public static <T> Procedure.Binary<T,​T,​java.util.List<T>> bfs​(Graph<T,​?> graph)
        Returns a shortest path procedure which: 
         ignores edge weights
 uses breadth-first search to visit nodes
 has runtime O(V + E), space O(V) (V = number of nodes, E = number of edges)
        Type Parameters:
        T - node type
        Parameters:
        graph - graph to get shortest path from
        Returns:
        procedure which gets shortest path using breadth-first search

        Returns a shortest path procedure which: 
         respects edge weights
 uses Dijkstra's algorithm to find a path

        Type Parameters:

        E - edge type
        Parameters:
        graph - graph to get shortest path from
        adder - adds 2 edges together
